        </div>
        <div class="fa">+</div>
        <div class="fn">
          <div class="fi" style="background:#F5F3FF">
            <span style="font-size:22px">☕</span>
          </div>
          <div class="fl">Custom JARs updated</div>
          <div class="fs">Plugins + JDBC</div>
        </div>
        <div class="fa">→</div>
        <div class="fn">
          <div class="fi" style="background:#FEF3E2"><svg
              style="width:30px;height:30px;filter:invert(38%) sepia(60%) saturate(700%) hue-rotate(355deg)"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <use href="#jenkins" />
            </svg></div>
          <div class="fl">Jenkins Build 2</div>
          <div class="fs">Plugin Pipeline</div>
        </div>
        <div class="fa">→</div>
        <div class="fn">
          <div class="fi" style="background:#F0FDF4"><svg
              style="width:30px;height:30px;filter:invert(40%) sepia(70%) saturate(600%) hue-rotate(80deg)"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <use href="#jfrog" />
            </svg></div>
          <div class="fl">hop-sge published</div>
          <div class="fs">Artifactory</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid">
        <!-- Build 1 explanation -->
        <div class="fc">
          <div class="fc-hd">
            <div class="fc-icon" style="background:#FFF3E0">
              <div class="fi-hop" style="width:19px;height:19px;font-size:7px;border-radius:4px">Hop</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="fc-fn">Build 1 — Hop Version Update</div>
              <div class="fc-tag">Triggered when Apache Hop releases a new version (e.g. 2.15 → 2.16)</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="fc-bd">
            <div class="fc-what">Downloads the new Apache Hop distribution, installs it into a UBI base image, and
              publishes it as <code
                style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;background:#F1F5F9;padding:1px 4px;border-radius:3px">hop-base</code>.
              This image contains only the vanilla Hop engine — no custom plugins yet.</div>
            <div class="rule yes">
              <div class="rd"></div>
              <div>Starts from a hardened UBI base image</div>
            </div>
            <div class="rule yes">
              <div class="rd"></div>
              <div>Installs the specific Hop version (pinned, never <code
                  style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px">latest</code>)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="rule yes">
              <div class="rd"></div>
              <div>Sets up <code style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px">/opt/hop</code> directory
                structure</div>
            </div>
            <div class="rule yes">
              <div class="rd"></div>
              <div>Tags as <code style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px">hop-base:2.16-v1</code>
                and pushes to
                Artifactory</div>
            </div>
            <div class="note n-blue" style="margin-top:8px">
              <div class="n-lbl">How often does this run?</div>
              <div class="n-txt">Rarely — only when you decide to adopt a new Hop release. It's a deliberate,
                planned upgrade, not an automatic trigger.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Build 2 explanation -->
        <div class="fc">
          <div class="fc-hd">
            <div class="fc-icon" style="background:#F5F3FF">
              <span style="font-size:15px">☕</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="fc-fn">Build 2 — Custom Plugins &amp; JDBC</div>
              <div class="fc-tag">Triggered when you update custom JARs or JDBC drivers in Bitbucket</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="fc-bd">
            <div class="fc-what">Runs <code
                style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;background:#F1F5F9;padding:1px 4px;border-radius:3px">mvn
                clean package</code> to build your custom plugin JARs, then layers them on top of the latest
              <code
                style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;background:#F1F5F9;padding:1px 4px;border-radius:3px">hop-base</code>
              image along with any JDBC drivers. The output is the final <code
                style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;background:#F1F5F9;padding:1px 4px;border-radius:3px">hop-sge</code>
              image that all application Dockerfiles inherit from.
            </div>
            <div class="rule yes">
              <div class="rd"></div>
              <div>Builds custom plugins with Maven (<code
                  style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px">mvn clean package</code>)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="rule yes">
              <div class="rd"></div>
              <div>Copies plugin JARs into <code
                  style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px">/opt/hop/plugins/</code></div>
            </div>
            <div class="rule yes">
              <div class="rd"></div>
              <div>Copies JDBC drivers into <code
                  style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px">/opt/hop/lib/jdbc/</code></div>
            </div>
            <div class="rule yes">
              <div class="rd"></div>
              <div>Tags as <code style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px">hop-sge:2.16-v1</code>
                and pushes to
                Artifactory</div>
            </div>
            <div class="note n-amber" style="margin-top:8px">
              <div class="n-lbl">Rebuild cascade</div>
              <div class="n-txt">When hop-sge gets a new version tag, all downstream application images should be
                rebuilt to pick up the updated runtime. Jenkins can trigger this automatically.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

