        <div class="note n-green">
          <div class="n-lbl">The two-stage guarantee</div>
          <div class="n-txt">Build 1 (Hop version) produces <code
              style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px">hop-base</code>. Build 2 (plugins) layers
            your custom JARs on top and produces <code
              style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px">hop-sge</code>. Your application Dockerfile
            always inherits from <code style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px">hop-sge</code> —
            never from hop-base
            directly.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="note n-amber">
          <div class="n-lbl">When to rebuild what</div>
          <div class="n-txt"><strong>New Hop version?</strong> → Run Build 1, which auto-triggers Build 2, which
            notifies teams to rebuild app images.<br><strong>New plugin or JDBC JAR?</strong> → Run Build 2 only — the
            Hop version stays the same, just the plugins change.<br><strong>Updated app code?</strong> → Run your normal
            app pipeline (Step 6) — hop-sge doesn't change.</div>
        </div>
